y path.</p>\n<p>These commands fix it.</p>\n<pre><code>cd /usr/local/cuda/lib64 \\\n &amp;&amp; mv stubs/libcuda.so ./ \\\n &amp;&amp; ln -s libcuda.so libcuda.so.1 \\\n &amp;&amp; ldconfig\n</code></pre>\n<p>Please fix that bug in docker image.</p>", "body_text": "Im running tensorflow with cuda in a docker container as an instance of tensorflow/tensorflow:latest-gpu-py3.\nWhen import tensorflow in a python3 terminal, it throws an error because libcuda.so.1 not in library path.\nThese commands fix it.\ncd /usr/local/cuda/lib64 \\\n && mv stubs/libcuda.so ./ \\\n && ln -s libcuda.so libcuda.so.1 \\\n && ldconfig\n\nPlease fix that bug in docker image.", "body": "Im running tensorflow with cuda in a docker container as an instance of tensorflow/tensorflow:latest-gpu-py3.\r\n\r\nWhen `import tensorflow` in a python3 terminal, it throws an error because libcuda.so.1 not in library path.\r\n\r\nThese commands fix it. \r\n```\r\ncd /usr/local/cuda/lib64 \\\r\n && mv stubs/libcuda.so ./ \\\r\n && ln -s libcuda.so libcuda.so.1 \\\r\n && ldconfig\r\n```\r\n\r\nPlease fix that bug in docker image.\r\n"}